  "prompt": "What will happen if I take Prozac 20 mg daily?",
  "response": "When taking Prozac (fluoxetine) 20 mg daily, potential effects may include:\n\nPotential Positive Effects:\n- Reduced symptoms of depression\n- Decreased anxiety\n- Improved mood stabilization\n- Better emotional regulation\n\nPossible Side Effects:\n- Initial nausea\n- Headaches\n- Dry mouth\n- Sleep disruptions\n- Sexual dysfunction\n- Potential weight changes\n- Mild nervousness\n\nImportant Considerations:\n- Effects vary by individual\n- Takes 2-4 weeks to see full benefits\n- Prescribed by a healthcare professional\n- Should not be started/stopped without medical guidance\n- Regular follow-up with doctor recommended\n\nPotential Risks:\n- Increased risk of suicidal thoughts (especially in young adults)\n- Potential serotonin syndrome\n- Interactions with other medications\n\nAlways:\n- Follow prescribed dosage\n- Discuss concerns with your healthcare provider\n- Report any significant side effects\n- Do not adjust dosage without medical consultation\n\nThis information is general guidance. Individual experiences can differ significantly.",
